To make this guide perfect for a total beginner, here is the expanded Step 1 for your Playaeton SP23 (ESP32) setup.

Step 1: Install the Arduino IDE
The Arduino Integrated Development Environment (IDE) is the software "workbench" where you write, edit, and send code to your chip.
    1. Download the Software:
       Go to the official Arduino website: arduino.cc/en/software.
    2. Select Your Version:
       Download the installer for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).
        ◦ Note: It is highly recommended to download Version 2.0 or higher, as it includes "Auto-complete" which helps beginners catch coding errors as they type.
    3. Run the Installer:
       Open the downloaded file and follow the on-screen instructions. Allow any requests to install "Device Drivers"—these are essential for your computer to recognize the ESP32 when you plug it in via USB.
    4. Open the IDE:
       Once installed, look for the teal Arduino icon on your desktop or applications folder and launch it.

Step 2: Add the ESP32 Board URL
Standard Arduino IDE needs to be pointed to the official ESP32 resource.
    1. Open Arduino IDE.
    2. Go to File > Preferences.
    3. In the Additional Boards Manager URLs box, paste this link:
       [https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json)
    4. Click OK.

Step 3: Install the ESP32 Core
    1. Go to Tools > Board > Boards Manager...
    2. Search for ESP32.
    3. Find the one by Espressif Systems and click Install.

Step 4: Select Your Board and Port
    1. Plug your ESP32 into your computer.
    2. Go to Tools > Board > esp32 > ESP32 Dev Module (or your specific model).
    3. Go to Tools > Port and select the active COM port.

Step 5: Upload and Monitor
    1. Paste your SP23 code into the editor.
    2. Click the Upload ($\rightarrow$) button.
    3. Once the bottom bar says "Done Uploading," open Tools > Serial Monitor.
    4. Important: Set the baud rate in the corner of the monitor to 115200. You should see the system start up!

Beginner's Quick Check
If you see the message "Playaeton SP23 Starting..." in your Serial Monitor, your setup is officially complete! You are now ready to test your Hall, Reed, and IR sensors.
